                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d24">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.248/261: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-17T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 17, 1942—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>110. 1. Have you seen General Magruder’s strictly confidential telegraphic report
                    to the War Department of February 10 in regard to the general military situation
                    in China and related matters? If not, please ask General Magruder to show you a
                    copy.</p>
                <p>2. Department would appreciate your comments on General Magruder’s report.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
